All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
Arc
The 'Arc' class represents a connection between a Place and a Transition in a Petri net.
DrainerArc
The 'DrainerArc' class represents a specialized type of Arc that drains tokens from a Place when activated.
IPetriNetwork
The 'IPetriNetwork' interface defines the methods that a Petri net network should implement.
PetriNetwork
The 'PetriNetwork' class represents a Petri net with places, transitions, and arcs.
Place
The 'Place' class represents a location in a Petri net where tokens can be stored.
Transition
The 'Transition' class represents a state in a Petri net where a firing event can occur.
ZeroArc
The 'ZeroArc' class represents a specialized type of Arc that does not contribute to token flow.
